Senior Performance-Based Maintenance Expert




NTU International is preparing a proposal for the EU-funded project “Technical Assistance to ECOWAS in Transport Governance”, which aims to strengthen sustainable, smart, resilient and safe mobility systems across the ECOWAS region in West Africa. The project will support ECOWAS institutions, Member States, and regional stakeholders in improving transport governance, corridor management, infrastructure planning, climate resilience, and regional connectivity.

The Technical Assistance will support ECOWAS and Member States in promoting efficient and sustainable road maintenance practices, including the development and implementation of performance-based maintenance systems and modern maintenance procurement approaches.

NTU International is seeking a Senior Performance-Based Maintenance Expert to support the development and implementation of performance-based road maintenance systems, contracts, and maintenance financing approaches across the ECOWAS region.




Key Responsibilities

Support the design and implementation of performance-based road maintenance systems and contracting approaches;
Provide technical assistance on maintenance procurement, contract management, and contractor performance monitoring;
Develop performance indicators, service levels, and maintenance monitoring frameworks;
Support preparation of bidding documents, technical specifications, and contract documentation for maintenance contracts;
Advise on maintenance planning, budgeting, and performance monitoring systems;
Support the development of transparent and efficient maintenance procurement procedures;
Contribute to climate-resilient and sustainable maintenance approaches for regional and national road networks;
Coordinate with ECOWAS institutions, national road agencies, contractors, and development partners;
Deliver technical workshops, training sessions, and capacity-building activities related to performance-based maintenance systems;
Contribute to monitoring, reporting, and evaluation of maintenance performance and contract implementation.




Education

Master’s degree in civil engineering, transport infrastructure, construction management, procurement, or another relevant field.




General Professional Experience

Minimum 10 years of professional experience in road maintenance, transport infrastructure management, or maintenance contract implementation;
Proven experience working on transport infrastructure projects in developing countries, preferably in Sub-Saharan Africa;
Experience in international development cooperation and donor-funded programmes.




Specific Professional Experience

Minimum 7 years of experience in performance-based road maintenance systems or maintenance contract management;
Demonstrated experience with output- and performance-based road contracts, maintenance procurement, and contractor supervision;
Experience with FIDIC-based maintenance contracts or similar international contracting frameworks is considered an advantage;
Experience supporting road maintenance programmes financed by the EU, World Bank, AfDB, EIB, or other international financial institutions is considered a strong asset;
Experience with road asset management systems, maintenance auditing, or performance monitoring tools is considered an asset;
Experience working with road agencies, transport ministries, or regional organisations is an advantage.




Languages

English or French (C1 mandatory);
Working knowledge of the other language is considered an asset.




Please note that inclusion in the expert pool does not guarantee immediate assignment. Experts will be contacted based on project requirements and matching qualifications. Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.

Senior Climate-Resilient Infrastructure Expert




NTU International is preparing a proposal for the EU-funded project “Technical Assistance to ECOWAS in Transport Governance”, which aims to strengthen sustainable, smart, resilient and safe mobility systems across the ECOWAS region in West Africa. The project will support ECOWAS institutions, Member States, and regional stakeholders in improving transport governance, corridor management, infrastructure planning, climate resilience, and regional connectivity.

The Technical Assistance will support the integration of climate resilience and climate-proofing approaches into transport infrastructure planning, corridor development, road asset management, and regional transport governance systems across West Africa.

NTU International is seeking a Senior Climate-Resilient Infrastructure Expert to support climate adaptation, resilience mainstreaming, and sustainable infrastructure planning for regional transport systems across the ECOWAS region.




Key Responsibilities

Support the integration of climate resilience and climate adaptation measures into transport infrastructure projects and corridor initiatives;
Provide technical assistance on climate-proofing methodologies, disaster risk reduction, and resilient infrastructure design;
Conduct climate vulnerability assessments, resilience analyses, and climate risk screening for transport infrastructure projects;
Support the development of climate-resilient infrastructure standards, technical guidelines, and operational frameworks;
Advise ECOWAS institutions and Member States on resilient transport infrastructure planning and climate adaptation strategies;
Contribute to the integration of environmental sustainability, social inclusion, and resilience considerations into infrastructure projects;
Support the preparation of technical studies, resilience assessments, policy recommendations, and climate adaptation strategies;
Coordinate with transport authorities, environmental agencies, development partners, and regional stakeholders;
Deliver workshops, technical training, and capacity-building activities related to climate-resilient infrastructure and adaptation planning;
Contribute to monitoring, reporting, and analytical outputs related to resilience and climate adaptation initiatives.




Education

Master’s degree in civil engineering, climate change, environmental engineering, infrastructure resilience, disaster risk management, or another relevant field.




General Professional Experience

Minimum 10 years of professional experience in climate resilience, infrastructure adaptation, transport engineering, or sustainable infrastructure development;
Proven experience working on infrastructure or transport projects in developing countries, preferably in Sub-Saharan Africa;
Experience in international development cooperation and donor-funded programmes.




Specific Professional Experience

Minimum 7 years of experience in climate-resilient infrastructure, climate adaptation, or disaster risk management related to transport or infrastructure sectors;
Demonstrated experience with climate vulnerability assessments, resilience screening, or climate-proofing of infrastructure projects;
Experience related to transport corridors, road infrastructure, bridge infrastructure, or regional connectivity projects is considered an advantage;
Experience supporting projects financed by the EU, World Bank, AfDB, EIB, Green Climate Fund, or other international financial institutions is considered a strong asset;
Experience integrating climate resilience into infrastructure planning, asset management, or engineering standards is considered an asset;
Experience working with government institutions, regional organisations, or infrastructure agencies is considered an advantage.




Languages

English or French (C1 mandatory);
Working knowledge of the other language is considered an asset.




Please note that inclusion in the expert pool does not guarantee immediate assignment. Experts will be contacted based on project requirements and matching qualifications. Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.

Senior AI / Digital Transformation Expert




NTU International is preparing a proposal for the EU-funded project “Technical Assistance to ECOWAS in Transport Governance”, which aims to strengthen sustainable, smart, resilient and safe mobility systems across the ECOWAS region in West Africa. The project will support ECOWAS institutions, Member States, and regional stakeholders in improving transport governance, corridor management, infrastructure planning, climate resilience, and regional connectivity.

The Technical Assistance will support the digital transformation of transport governance systems across the ECOWAS region through the integration of artificial intelligence, digital platforms, smart monitoring systems, and data-driven decision-making tools.

NTU International is seeking a Senior AI / Digital Transformation Expert to support digital transformation initiatives, AI integration, smart transport systems, and innovation-driven governance solutions across West Africa.




Key Responsibilities

Support the development and implementation of digital transformation strategies and smart transport governance solutions;
Provide technical assistance on the integration of artificial intelligence and digital technologies into transport, logistics, and infrastructure systems;
Support the development of AI-enabled monitoring tools, predictive analytics systems, and digital decision-support platforms;
Advise on automation, digital interoperability, data governance, and innovation frameworks for transport governance systems;
Support digitalisation initiatives related to corridor monitoring, customs systems, road safety, transport observatories, and infrastructure management;
Contribute to the preparation of digital transformation strategies, technical specifications, innovation roadmaps, and operational guidelines;
Promote the use of emerging technologies and data-driven approaches to improve transport governance and regional connectivity;
Coordinate with ECOWAS institutions, ICT providers, transport agencies, and development partners;
Deliver workshops, technical training, and capacity-building activities related to AI applications and digital transformation in the transport sector;
Contribute to monitoring, reporting, and analytical outputs related to digital innovation and AI integration initiatives.




Education

Master’s degree in computer science, artificial intelligence, information systems, digital innovation, data science, or another relevant field.




General Professional Experience

Minimum 10 years of professional experience in digital transformation, information systems, artificial intelligence, or smart infrastructure systems;
Proven experience working on digitalisation or infrastructure sector projects in developing countries, preferably in Sub-Saharan Africa;
Experience in international development cooperation and donor-funded programmes.




Specific Professional Experience

Minimum 7 years of experience in digital transformation, AI systems, smart governance platforms, or digital innovation projects;
Demonstrated experience with AI applications, automation systems, predictive analytics, digital monitoring tools, or data-driven decision-support systems;
Experience related to transport systems, logistics, infrastructure management, customs digitalisation, or smart mobility initiatives is considered an advantage;
Experience supporting projects financed by the EU, World Bank, AfDB, EIB, or other international financial institutions is considered a strong asset;
Experience with interoperability frameworks, digital governance systems, or public sector digitalisation initiatives is considered an asset;
Experience coordinating with public institutions, ICT providers, innovation ecosystems, or regional organisations is considered an advantage.




Languages

English or French (C1 mandatory);
Working knowledge of the other language is considered an asset.




Please note that inclusion in the expert pool does not guarantee immediate assignment. Experts will be contacted based on project requirements and matching qualifications. Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.

Senior Customs Digitalisation / Transit Systems Expert




NTU International is preparing a proposal for the EU-funded project “Technical Assistance to ECOWAS in Transport Governance”, which aims to strengthen sustainable, smart, resilient and safe mobility systems across the ECOWAS region in West Africa. The project will support ECOWAS institutions, Member States, and regional stakeholders in improving transport governance, corridor management, infrastructure planning, climate resilience, and regional connectivity.

The Technical Assistance will support the digitalisation and interconnection of customs and transit systems across the ECOWAS region, including deployment of digital tools, interoperability mechanisms, and corridor monitoring systems to improve trade facilitation and regional transport efficiency.

NTU International is seeking a Senior Customs Digitalisation / Transit Systems Expert to support customs digitalisation, transit management systems, interoperability frameworks, and regional customs integration initiatives across West Africa.




Key Responsibilities

Support the digitalisation and interconnection of customs and transit systems across ECOWAS Member States;
Provide technical assistance on customs IT systems, transit management platforms, and interoperability frameworks;
Support implementation and operationalisation of regional transit systems, including SIGMAT and related digital customs platforms;
Advise on digital customs procedures, real-time data exchange systems, and corridor monitoring tools;
Support development and deployment of digital solutions for customs assessment, payment systems, and border control processes;
Facilitate interoperability between national customs systems and regional digital platforms;
Contribute to the preparation of technical specifications, system assessments, operational guidelines, and digitalisation strategies;
Coordinate with customs authorities, transport institutions, IT providers, and regional stakeholders;
Deliver technical workshops, training sessions, and capacity-building activities related to customs digitalisation and transit systems;
Contribute to monitoring, reporting, and analytical outputs related to digital customs systems and regional interoperability initiatives.




Education

Master’s degree in information systems, customs administration, computer science, transport logistics, international trade, or another relevant field.




General Professional Experience

Minimum 10 years of professional experience in customs digitalisation, transit systems, information systems, or trade facilitation;
Proven experience working on customs, transport, or regional integration projects in developing countries, preferably in Sub-Saharan Africa;
Experience in international development cooperation and donor-funded programmes.




Specific Professional Experience

Minimum 7 years of experience in customs IT systems, digital transit systems, or customs interoperability initiatives;
Demonstrated experience with SIGMAT, customs management systems, trade facilitation platforms, or regional digitalisation projects;
Experience with digital border systems, electronic cargo tracking, or corridor monitoring systems is considered an advantage;
Experience working with ECOWAS, UEMOA, AfCFTA, WCO, or other regional customs and trade facilitation frameworks is considered a strong asset;
Experience supporting projects financed by the EU, World Bank, AfDB, EIB, or other international financial institutions is considered an asset;
Experience coordinating with customs administrations, ICT providers, or regional institutions is considered an advantage.




Languages

English or French (C1 mandatory);
Working knowledge of the other language is considered an asset.




Please note that inclusion in the expert pool does not guarantee immediate assignment. Experts will be contacted based on project requirements and matching qualifications. Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.

About IFDC

The International Fertilizer Development Center (IFDC) is a public international organization that advances soil health and strengthens agricultural systems through science-based innovation. For over 50 years, IFDC has translated research into practical solutions that improve nutrient use efficiency, restore degraded soils, strengthen local agricultural markets and expand opportunity for smallholder farmers, especially women and youth.

We work with farmers, governments and private sector partners to build resilient farming systems that produce nutritious food, improve livelihoods, and safeguard natural resources for future generations.

Our Values

We Are Guided By Four Core Principles

Collaborate - We work across teams, countries and partners to create lasting impact.

Innovate - We apply evidence and continuous learning to design practical and responsible solutions.

Include - We promote equity and meaningful participation for women, youth and underrepresented groups.

Act with Integrity - We steward resources responsibly, uphold transparency and remain accountable to the communities, partners, staff and donors who place their trust in us.

Responsibilities


Ensure the program implementation activities in-country are in line with the overall vision and leadership of the program; 
Support the program’s leadership and the consortium partners to build and manage a strong implementation team in-country with a clear strategy to deliver results;
Create and maintain good working relationships with implementing partners and other relevant projects and programs in-country and ensure adequate leverage and synergy between these implementing partners and projects/programs;
Represent the program in meetings, conferences, and other opportunities conducive to publicizing, promoting and marketing the project’s (and project partners’) achievements in country;
Participate or lead regular project management meetings with representatives of consortium members and with the donor embassy representatives at country level;
Ensure consistency among activities implemented in-country and compliance with national sector specific strategy and policies; 
Monitor project overall expenditure and private sector contribution against budgets and ensure financial compliance to both donor requirements and IFDC procedures; 
Supervise completion of timely and high-quality work plans, progress reports and financial reports; 
Organize the project's monthly cash flow needs and submit a request for advance funds accordingly;
Monitor project indicators in accordance with the Performance Monitoring and Evaluation Plan, evaluate program results and take necessary corrective actions whenever needed; 
Collaborate with IFDC leadership to ensure that managerial, administrative, and financial procedures comply with provisions of the project contract; 
Monitor in-country program budget and ensure a desirable budget burn rate;
Perform other roles necessary or those to be assigned to you by IFDC leadership.


Requirements


Bachelor’s degree in Agronomy, Seed Science, Soil Science, Agricultural Economics, International Development, or a related field;
A minimum of 10 years of hands-on experience in seed sector and agricultural development (seed breeding, production and distribution, soil science, agronomy, agriculture financing mechanisms, etc.), with a sizable portion of this experience in West Africa (especially Mali, Burkina Faso or Niger);
Proven record of accomplishment and expertise in seed sector overall management, with a deep knowledge of main seed international and local stakeholders, and good understanding of sustainable agricultural practices;
Established and active relationships with key stakeholders in a target country both in the research, farmer organizations, and public and private sectors, related to seed and agricultural development and soil fertility;
Experience in developing partnerships with a diverse range of stakeholders, including non-governments and government entities (e.g. private sector actors, and development partners);
Fluent in both French and English, enabling effective communication and collaboration in multicultural settings;
Exceptional communication skills, both written and verbal, to effectively convey project objectives and achievements.


Reporting and Work Relationships

The Country Coordinator is supervised by and reports to the Deputy Program Director - Technical with regular collaboration with the Deputy Program Director - Operation and Components Leads. The Country Coordinator will also collaborate with the Country IFDC leadership and other program leads in-country.

Location

This role is for nationally recruited staff and is based in IFDC office in Burkina Faso.

Benefits

IFDC's benefits include annual and sick leave, health and group life insurance coverage, a 13th-month salary, social security and pension contribution in compliance with local laws and end-of-contract benefits.

Salary Clause

The salary grade for this position is BG 9 with a salary of 1,832,407 XOF.

The determination of new employee salaries considers numerous factors. These include the salary range linked to the assigned job grade, the candidate's qualifications in relation to the job's responsibilities and prerequisites, internal fairness, the competitive state of the job market, as well as potential organizational and budgetary considerations.

Diversity Clause

IFDC is committed to fostering a culture of diversity, equity, and inclusion. We believe in the value of bringing together people with a broad range of backgrounds, experiences, and perspectives. All employment decisions at IFDC are made on the basis of ability, performance, and organizational need, in alignment with our values of fairness, respect, and opportunity for all.

The recruitment for the position of Country Coordinator is being conducted in support of an ongoing proposal effort in the Sahel region.

