Master’s degree in law, transport law, public policy, international law, or another relevant field.




General Professional Experience

Minimum 10 years of professional experience in legal and regulatory reform, public sector governance, or transport sector legislation;
Proven experience working on infrastructure, transport, or regional integration projects in developing countries, preferably in Sub-Saharan Africa;
Experience in international development cooperation and donor-funded programmes.




