PURPOSE & OBJECTIVE




Under the Planning Manager's responsibility, the Senior Ventilation Engineer will design, plan, track, and report on all ventilation activities in accordance with safety standards.




KEY ACCOUNTABILITIES




Conduct daily vent surveys ;
Prepare monthly ventilation reports ;
Update monthly Ventilation Model ;
Review monthly plans and organize UG ventilation requirements ;
Provide Quarterly and LOM ventilation planning ;
Prepare annual and quarterly ventilation cost forecasting ;
Provide end of quarter reporting ;
Provide improvement initiatives ;
Ensure supervision and mentoring of ventilation engineers.




SKILLS, KNOWLEDGE & EXPERIENCE




Education:

Degree in mining engineering or equivalent.




Relevant experience:

Minimum 3 years of underground mining experience in a similar position.
Knowing how to read and write in French and English.
Be proactive, dynamic, rigorous, with a high sense of ethics and discretion.
Have skills in leadership, communication, decision-making, problem-solving, and hazard identification.
Be able to identify any hazard and be able to implement controls to eliminate or minimize the risk.
Demonstrate availability even after working hours.
The ability to manage several projects and tasks at the same time.
A reputation for integrity and ethics.
Demonstrated supervisory skills.

