Contribute to the preparation of corridor performance reports, analytical studies, and logistics assessments;
Support monitoring of key indicators including border crossing times, transport costs, infrastructure conditions, and logistics efficiency;
Coordinate with ECOWAS institutions, customs authorities, transport agencies, corridor stakeholders, and development partners;
Deliver technical workshops, training sessions, and capacity-building activities related to corridor observatories and logistics monitoring;
Contribute to monitoring, reporting, and analytical outputs related to corridor performance and regional transport efficiency.




Education

Master’s degree in transport economics, logistics, data analytics, information systems, transport planning, or another relevant field.




General Professional Experience

